1
00:00:07,090 --> 00:00:09,217
I THOUGHT CAJUN FOOD WAS HOT.

2
00:00:14,765 --> 00:00:17,058
D'MARR?

3
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:20,270
W-WHAT DID YOU CALL
THAT...SPICE?

4
00:00:20,312 --> 00:00:21,897
HAJJLARAN.

5
00:00:21,939 --> 00:00:25,108
THE WARLORDS ON PREENOS USE IT
TO TEST THEIR COURAGE.

6
00:00:26,485 --> 00:00:28,320
YOU SURE YOU WON'T HAVE SOME?

7
00:00:28,362 --> 00:00:30,531
MY COURAGE DOESN'T NEED TESTING.

8
00:00:30,572 --> 00:00:32,366
I HAVE OTHER ITEMS TO TRADE.

9
00:00:32,407 --> 00:00:38,038
I CAN GET YOU SOME
TRIAXIAN SILK FOR, SAY...

10
00:00:38,079 --> 00:00:40,040
ANOTHER PROTEIN RESEQUENCER?

11
00:00:40,081 --> 00:00:43,042
I BET YOU'D LOOK GOOD
IN TRIAXIAN SILK.

12
00:00:43,084 --> 00:00:45,504
ARCHER: WHAT WE REALLY NEED
ARE ENGINEERING SUPPLIES.

13
00:00:45,546 --> 00:00:48,215
TUCKER: AHEM. RAW DURATANIUM,
DILITHIUM ORE.

14
00:00:48,256 --> 00:00:49,550
D'MARR: I'M SORRY.

15
00:00:49,591 --> 00:00:52,845
I PREFER TO DEAL
IN MORE...EXOTIC GOODS.

16
00:00:52,887 --> 00:00:57,391
BUT ABOUT TWO DAYS FROM HERE,
THERE'S A SMALL SYSTEM.

17
00:00:57,432 --> 00:00:59,267
YOU MIGHT FIND
WHAT YOU'RE LOOKING FOR THERE.

18
00:00:59,309 --> 00:01:01,603
WE HAVEN'T DETECTED
ANY INHABITED PLANETS

19
00:01:01,645 --> 00:01:02,938
ON LONG-RANGE SCANS.

20
00:01:02,980 --> 00:01:06,233
IT'S NOT INHABITED...
NOT EXACTLY.

21
00:01:07,275 --> 00:01:09,319
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

22
00:01:09,361 --> 00:01:10,487
MMM!

23
00:01:10,529 --> 00:01:11,697
THIS IS EXCELLENT.

24
00:01:11,739 --> 00:01:13,281
WHAT IS IT AGAIN?

25
00:01:13,323 --> 00:01:14,992
COFFEE.

26
00:01:15,034 --> 00:01:16,368
I CAN HAVE MY CHEF

27
00:01:16,410 --> 00:01:19,830
WRAP UP A FEW KILOGRAMS
FOR YOU...

28
00:01:19,872 --> 00:01:22,123
IF YOU WOULDN'T MIND TELLING US

29
00:01:22,165 --> 00:01:24,125
WHERE WE CAN FIND
THOSE SUPPLIES.

30
00:01:24,167 --> 00:01:26,003
CAPTAIN, PLEASE.

31
00:01:26,045 --> 00:01:28,714
THIS ISN'T A MATTER
OF NEGOTIATION.

32
00:01:28,756 --> 00:01:31,050
I'M THINKING OF YOUR SAFETY.

33
00:01:35,178 --> 00:01:36,430
10 KILOS?

34
00:01:36,471 --> 00:01:39,016
IT--IT'S PURE LUCK
THAT I EVEN FOUND IT.

35
00:01:39,058 --> 00:01:40,267
FOUND WHAT?

36
00:01:40,308 --> 00:01:41,643
D'MARR: A SHIP...

37
00:01:41,685 --> 00:01:44,103
CRASHED ON ONE
OF THE INNER PLANETS.

38
00:01:44,145 --> 00:01:45,564
THERE WERE NO LIFE-SIGNS ABOARD,

39
00:01:45,606 --> 00:01:49,860
SO I LANDED TO...CLAIM
MY RIGHTS OF SALVAGE.

40
00:01:49,902 --> 00:01:51,236
WHAT'D YOU FIND?

41
00:01:51,278 --> 00:01:54,406
D'MARR: A TRANSPORT VESSEL,
LARGELY INTACT.

42
00:01:54,448 --> 00:01:57,076
I COULD HAVE STRIPPED IT BARE
AND MADE A FORTUNE.

43
00:01:57,117 --> 00:01:58,702
WHY DIDN'T YOU?

44
00:01:58,744 --> 00:02:02,372
THE, UM, CREW OBJECTED.

45
00:02:02,414 --> 00:02:05,834
YOU SAID THERE WEREN'T
ANY LIFE-SIGNS ABOARD.

46
00:02:05,876 --> 00:02:07,711
THERE WEREN'T.

47
00:02:07,753 --> 00:02:11,256
THERE WASN'T<i> ANYTHING</i> ALIVE.

48
00:02:11,298 --> 00:02:15,218
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING--
THE SHIP WAS HAUNTED?

49
00:02:21,642 --> 00:02:26,271
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

50
00:02:26,313 --> 00:02:29,483
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

51
00:02:29,524 --> 00:02:33,361
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

52
00:02:33,403 --> 00:02:36,907
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

53
00:02:36,949 --> 00:02:41,411
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

54
00:02:41,453 --> 00:02:44,873
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

55
00:02:44,915 --> 00:02:48,877
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

56
00:02:48,919 --> 00:02:52,006
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

57
00:02:52,047 --> 00:02:54,716
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

58
00:02:54,758 --> 00:02:56,885
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

59
00:02:56,927 --> 00:02:59,805
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

60
00:02:59,847 --> 00:03:04,643
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

61
00:03:04,685 --> 00:03:07,896
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

62
00:03:07,938 --> 00:03:12,151
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

63
00:03:12,191 --> 00:03:15,362
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

64
00:03:15,403 --> 00:03:20,993
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

65
00:03:21,035 --> 00:03:23,037
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

66
00:03:23,078 --> 00:03:25,330
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

67
00:03:25,372 --> 00:03:28,917
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

68
00:03:28,959 --> 00:03:33,714
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

69
00:03:48,436 --> 00:03:50,605
THE ATMOSPHERE IS THIN
BUT BREATHABLE.

70
00:03:50,647 --> 00:03:51,982
ARCHER: ANY BIO-SIGNS?

71
00:03:52,024 --> 00:03:54,109
T'POL: AS THE TRADER SAID, NONE.

72
00:03:54,151 --> 00:03:55,986
I'VE LOCATED THE SHIP, SIR.

73
00:03:56,028 --> 00:03:58,739
LET'S SEE IT.

74
00:04:00,991 --> 00:04:02,826
T'POL: NO POWER SIGNATURES.

75
00:04:02,868 --> 00:04:04,661
IT APPEARS TO BE DESERTED.

76
00:04:04,703 --> 00:04:07,915
BUT ARE YOUR SENSORS
CALIBRATED FOR GHOSTS?

77
00:04:07,956 --> 00:04:09,958
TUCKER: SO FAR, D'MARR'S BATTING
A THOUSAND.

78
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:14,129
I'M READING DURATANIUM,
BERYLLIUM, AND...DILITHIUM.

79
00:04:14,171 --> 00:04:15,839
I WONDER WHAT CAUSED THE CRASH.

80
00:04:15,881 --> 00:04:18,050
THERE'S NO WAY TO TELL
WITHOUT A CLOSER LOOK.

81
00:04:18,092 --> 00:04:19,676
TUCKER: LET'S GET DOWN THERE.

82
00:04:19,718 --> 00:04:21,511
MAYWEATHER: ARE WE SURE
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA?

83
00:04:21,553 --> 00:04:24,014
HOSHI: YOU'RE NOT AFRAID
IT'S REALLY HAUNTED, ARE YOU?

84
00:04:24,056 --> 00:04:27,142
MAYWEATHER: WE DON'T KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO THE CREW.

85
00:04:27,184 --> 00:04:30,229
THAT SHIP COULD BE A TOMB.

86
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:31,813
YOU REALLY THINK WE SHOULD BE
PICKING THROUGH IT

87
00:04:31,855 --> 00:04:33,440
FOR SPARE PARTS, SIR?

88
00:04:33,481 --> 00:04:36,276
TUCKER: D'MARR DIDN'T SAY
ANYTHING ABOUT BODIES.

89
00:04:36,317 --> 00:04:38,737
CAPTAIN, WE'VE TAKEN
MORE DAMAGE OUT HERE

90
00:04:38,779 --> 00:04:40,155
THAN WE EVER EXPECTED TO.

91
00:04:40,197 --> 00:04:41,698
THERE'S ENOUGH DURATANIUM
DOWN THERE

92
00:04:41,740 --> 00:04:44,159
TO PATCH A LOT
OF HULL FRACTURES.

93
00:04:46,161 --> 00:04:48,038
ARCHER: LET'S PAY HER A VISIT.

94
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:51,416
IF WE FEEL THE SPIRITS DON'T
WANT US THERE, WE'LL LEAVE.

95
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:52,667
MALCOLM, YOU HAVE THE BRIDGE.

96
00:04:52,709 --> 00:04:53,835
REED: AYE, SIR.

97
00:04:53,877 --> 00:04:56,546
ARCHER: TRAVIS, YOU'RE DRIVING.

98
00:05:21,029 --> 00:05:23,031
ARCHER: T'POL?

99
00:05:23,073 --> 00:05:25,242
T'POL: NOTHING.

100
00:05:25,284 --> 00:05:29,079
TUCKER: ACCORDING TO D'MARR,
ENGINEERING SHOULD BE THAT WAY.

101
00:05:29,121 --> 00:05:30,831
ARCHER: YOU AND T'POL
CHECK IT OUT.

102
00:05:30,872 --> 00:05:34,626
COM US IF YOU FIND
ANYTHING WE CAN USE...

103
00:05:34,668 --> 00:05:36,837
OR IF YOU...

104
00:05:36,878 --> 00:05:39,464
SEE ANY SIGNS OF THE CREW.

105
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:41,675
TUCKER: AYE, CAPTAIN.

106
00:05:51,643 --> 00:05:54,062
ARCHER: EVERYTHING OK, TRAVIS?

107
00:05:54,104 --> 00:05:55,897
MAYWEATHER: YES, SIR.

108
00:05:55,939 --> 00:05:57,356
I WAS JUST WONDERING,

109
00:05:57,398 --> 00:05:59,860
IF THAT TRADER LEFT
IN SUCH A HURRY,

110
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:02,988
WHY'D HE BOTHER TO CLOSE
THE HATCH BEHIND HIM?

111
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:35,729
[ CLICKING ]

112
00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:37,356
TUCKER: WHAT IS IT?

113
00:06:37,438 --> 00:06:39,900
T'POL: I HEARD SOMETHING.

114
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:43,528
TUCKER: RATS, MAYBE?

115
00:06:47,448 --> 00:06:49,617
T'POL: NO.

116
00:06:49,659 --> 00:06:52,204
TUCKER: WELL, THEN YOU
PROBABLY IMAGINED IT.

117
00:06:54,122 --> 00:06:56,415
T'POL: VULCANS
DON'T IMAGINE THINGS.

118
00:06:56,457 --> 00:06:59,002
TUCKER: IT'S NOTHING
TO BE ASHAMED OF.

119
00:06:59,044 --> 00:07:01,129
A SPOOKY SHIP, A MISSING CREW,

120
00:07:01,171 --> 00:07:03,757
THINGS GOING BUMP
IN THE NIGHT--

121
00:07:03,798 --> 00:07:06,385
GIVE ANYBODY THE CREEPS.

122
00:07:10,305 --> 00:07:12,182
THE CREEPS?

123
00:07:12,224 --> 00:07:15,269
TUCKER: YEAH, WILLIES.
HEEBIE-JEEBIES.

124
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:18,688
WHAT, DON'T YOU GET FRIGHTENED
EVERY ONCE IN A WHILE?

125
00:07:18,730 --> 00:07:20,399
NO.

126
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,025
TUCKER: NOT BY ANYTHING?

127
00:07:22,067 --> 00:07:23,193
NO.

128
00:07:23,235 --> 00:07:25,737
TUCKER: TOO BAD.

129
00:07:25,779 --> 00:07:28,282
NOTHING LIKE A GOOD SCARE.

130
00:07:33,078 --> 00:07:34,704
MAYWEATHER: WHAT DO YOU THINK
THAT TRADER

131
00:07:34,746 --> 00:07:36,415
REALLY SAW DOWN HERE, SIR?

132
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:38,166
ARCHER: I DON'T KNOW.

133
00:07:38,208 --> 00:07:42,296
MAYBE...SOMEONE ELSE WANTED
TO SALVAGE THIS WRECK

134
00:07:42,337 --> 00:07:44,714
AND THEY WERE TRYING
TO SCARE HIM OFF.

135
00:07:44,756 --> 00:07:46,883
MAYWEATHER: THAT MAKES SENSE,
EXCEPT SCAVENGERS

136
00:07:46,925 --> 00:07:49,719
WOULD'VE STRIPPED
THIS SHIP TO THE KEEL.

137
00:07:49,761 --> 00:07:51,096
THIS ISN'T TURNING INTO ONE

138
00:07:51,138 --> 00:07:53,681
OF YOUR FAMOUS
GHOST STORIES, IS IT?

139
00:07:53,723 --> 00:07:56,768
-IT<i> WOULD</i> MAKE A GOOD ONE, SIR.
-[ CHUCKLES ]

140
00:07:59,354 --> 00:08:00,855
ARCHER: WHAT DO YOU THINK?

141
00:08:00,897 --> 00:08:03,317
COMPUTER TERMINAL?

142
00:08:07,904 --> 00:08:09,323
MAYWEATHER: YES, SIR.

143
00:08:09,364 --> 00:08:10,949
THERE'S NO POWER,

144
00:08:10,991 --> 00:08:13,327
BUT THE DATA MODULES
LOOK INTACT.

145
00:08:13,368 --> 00:08:15,120
ARCHER: LET'S GET THEM
BACK TO THE SHIP,

146
00:08:15,162 --> 00:08:17,538
SEE IF WE CAN FIND OUT
WHAT HAPPENED HERE.

147
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:19,749
TUCKER: IT'S DILITHIUM,
ALL RIGHT.

148
00:08:19,791 --> 00:08:21,835
[ BEEPING ]

149
00:08:23,086 --> 00:08:24,712
HUH.

150
00:08:24,754 --> 00:08:26,173
T'POL: SOMETHING WRONG?

151
00:08:26,214 --> 00:08:27,715
TUCKER: NO.

152
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:30,635
THE CRYSTALS ARE
IN PERFECT SHAPE.

153
00:08:30,677 --> 00:08:33,972
WOULDN'T BE THAT HARD TO GET
THIS SHIP FLYING AGAIN.

154
00:08:36,557 --> 00:08:37,851
WHAT IS IT?

155
00:08:37,892 --> 00:08:40,687
T'POL: THERE'S SOMEONE HERE.

156
00:08:40,728 --> 00:08:43,148
TUCKER: YOU SAID THERE
WEREN'T ANY BIO-SIGNS.

157
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:44,441
T'POL: THERE AREN'T.

158
00:08:44,483 --> 00:08:46,151
TUCKER: IF YOU'RE TRYING
TO SCARE ME,

159
00:08:46,193 --> 00:08:48,820
I APPRECIATE THE EFFORT, BUT...

160
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:52,407
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

161
00:08:52,449 --> 00:08:53,574
TUCKER TO CAPTAIN ARCHER.

162
00:08:53,616 --> 00:08:54,701
Archer: Go ahead.

163
00:08:54,742 --> 00:08:56,328
TUCKER: WE'RE NOT ALONE
DOWN HERE.

164
00:08:56,370 --> 00:08:58,663
Archer: We're on our way.

165
00:09:16,431 --> 00:09:19,351
T'POL: THERE'S A SPACE
BEHIND THIS BULKHEAD.

166
00:09:54,094 --> 00:09:56,596
TUCKER: WHY DIDN'T ANY OF THIS
SHOW UP ON SENSORS?

167
00:09:56,637 --> 00:09:58,348
T'POL: THERE APPEARS TO BE
A DAMPENING FIELD

168
00:09:58,390 --> 00:10:00,350
IN THIS SECTION OF THE SHIP.

169
00:10:00,392 --> 00:10:02,477
TUCKER: WHAT'S GENERATING IT?

170
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:04,645
T'POL: I'M READING
A POWER SOURCE,

171
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:07,190
BUT I CAN'T PINPOINT
ITS LOCATION.

172
00:10:07,232 --> 00:10:10,110
TUCKER: THEN LET'S DO
SOME PINPOINTING.

173
00:10:18,659 --> 00:10:20,620
HI.

174
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:26,418
SORRY. IT'S OK.

175
00:10:26,460 --> 00:10:29,212
I'M NOT GONNA HURT YOU.

176
00:10:29,254 --> 00:10:31,423
HEY! T'POL!

177
00:10:55,155 --> 00:10:57,073
MAN: WE WERE ON OUR WAY BACK
FROM OUR COLONY

178
00:10:57,115 --> 00:10:58,866
ON KOTARA BARATH.

179
00:10:58,908 --> 00:11:01,119
WE CAME UNDER ATTACK
AS WE PASSED THIS SYSTEM.

180
00:11:01,161 --> 00:11:02,454
ARCHER: WHO ATTACKED YOU?

181
00:11:02,496 --> 00:11:03,955
MAN: THEY DIDN'T INTRODUCE
THEMSELVES.

182
00:11:03,997 --> 00:11:05,748
THEY JUST OPENED FIRE.

183
00:11:05,790 --> 00:11:08,168
SECOND MAN: WE'RE A SUPPLY SHIP.
WE DON'T CARRY LARGE WEAPONS.

184
00:11:08,209 --> 00:11:10,003
WE TRIED TO DEFEND OURSELVES.

185
00:11:10,044 --> 00:11:12,130
THE CAPTAIN WAS ABLE TO MAKE
A CRASH LANDING.

186
00:11:12,172 --> 00:11:14,257
IT'S A MIRACLE
WE ALL SURVIVED.

187
00:11:14,299 --> 00:11:16,176
MAYWEATHER: DIDN'T YOU SEND OUT
A DISTRESS CALL?

188
00:11:16,217 --> 00:11:18,386
MAN: IF WE HAD, IT WOULD'VE LET
THE RAIDERS KNOW WHERE WE WERE.

189
00:11:18,428 --> 00:11:20,763
TUCKER: SO YOU SET UP THIS
DAMPENING FIELD TO HIDE?

190
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:22,182
WOMAN: WE WERE AFRAID

191
00:11:22,223 --> 00:11:24,434
THEY'D COME DOWN
AND FINISH WHAT THEY STARTED.

192
00:11:24,476 --> 00:11:26,394
T'POL: HOW LONG
HAVE YOU BEEN HERE?

193
00:11:26,436 --> 00:11:28,062
NEARLY THREE YEARS.

194
00:11:28,104 --> 00:11:29,481
ARCHER: THREE YEARS?

195
00:11:29,523 --> 00:11:32,108
YOU'VE MADE QUITE A HOME
FOR YOURSELVES HERE.

196
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:33,818
MAN: WELL, WE DIDN'T HAVE
MUCH CHOICE.

197
00:11:33,860 --> 00:11:35,612
WELL, YOU DO NOW.

198
00:11:35,654 --> 00:11:37,447
OUR SHIP IS BIG ENOUGH
FOR ALL OF YOU.

199
00:11:37,489 --> 00:11:39,698
WE CAN TAKE YOU HOME.

200
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:42,035
FIRST MAN: YOU'RE VERY GENEROUS,
CAPTAIN,

201
00:11:42,076 --> 00:11:44,621
BUT OUR WORLD
IS OVER A YEAR AWAY.

202
00:11:44,663 --> 00:11:46,705
MAYWEATHER: WELL, WE CAN'T
JUST LEAVE YOU HERE.

203
00:11:46,747 --> 00:11:50,251
MAN: AS YOU SAY, WE'VE MADE
A HOME FOR OURSELVES.

204
00:11:53,754 --> 00:11:55,507
WHAT ABOUT THEIR ENGINES?

205
00:11:55,549 --> 00:11:57,008
TUCKER: THEIR DILITHIUM MATRIX
IS STABLE.

206
00:11:57,050 --> 00:12:00,220
THEY'VE GOT PLENTY
OF ANTIMATTER RESERVES.

207
00:12:00,261 --> 00:12:02,763
I THINK WE CAN GET
THIS SHIP FLYING.

208
00:12:02,805 --> 00:12:05,933
WE'VE TRIED, BELIEVE ME.

209
00:12:07,894 --> 00:12:11,147
ARCHER: WE HAVE RESOURCES
YOU MAY NOT HAVE.

210
00:12:11,189 --> 00:12:14,108
IT'S WORTH A SHOT.

211
00:12:15,109 --> 00:12:17,362
THANK YOU, CAPTAIN.

212
00:12:23,535 --> 00:12:25,662
[ CLATTERING ]

213
00:12:51,521 --> 00:12:53,398
OHH!

214
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,774
[ SIGHS ]

215
00:12:55,816 --> 00:12:57,694
YOU STARTLED ME.

216
00:12:57,736 --> 00:12:59,987
THAT'S TWICE IN ONE DAY.

217
00:13:02,031 --> 00:13:04,951
YOU EVER SAY ANYTHING?

218
00:13:04,992 --> 00:13:07,912
UNLESS YOU'RE UNABLE
TO SAY ANYTHING,

219
00:13:07,954 --> 00:13:11,874
IN WHICH CASE I APOLOGIZE.

220
00:13:26,306 --> 00:13:28,891
[ WHIRRING ]

221
00:13:31,102 --> 00:13:33,938
WOMAN: DON'T TOUCH THAT!

222
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:37,734
THE POWER'S BEEN ROUTED TO OUR
LIVING AREA THROUGH THAT RELAY.

223
00:13:37,776 --> 00:13:39,444
IT'S VERY DANGEROUS.

224
00:13:39,486 --> 00:13:43,364
WELL, I'M GLAD YOU FINALLY
DECIDED TO SPEAK UP.

225
00:13:43,406 --> 00:13:44,865
THANKS.

226
00:13:44,907 --> 00:13:47,744
WOMAN: YOU'RE WELCOME.

227
00:13:47,786 --> 00:13:50,829
TUCKER: YOU, UH...

228
00:13:50,871 --> 00:13:54,041
KNOW A LOT ABOUT
YOUR SHIP'S SYSTEMS?

229
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:56,461
WOMAN: MY FATHER
IS THE ENGINEER.

230
00:13:56,503 --> 00:13:59,714
HE TAUGHT ME
HOW THINGS WORK.

231
00:13:59,756 --> 00:14:03,050
WELL, STICK AROUND, THEN.

232
00:14:03,092 --> 00:14:04,385
YOU CAN WARN ME
ABOUT WHATEVER ELSE

233
00:14:04,427 --> 00:14:06,596
I NEED TO KEEP
MY HANDS OFF OF.

234
00:14:06,638 --> 00:14:08,014
SECOND WOMAN: HE'S BUSY.

235
00:14:08,055 --> 00:14:10,391
DON'T BOTHER HIM, LIANA.

236
00:14:12,226 --> 00:14:14,187
TUCKER: IT'S OK.

237
00:14:14,228 --> 00:14:15,730
I COULD USE THE COMPANY.

238
00:14:15,772 --> 00:14:18,650
MY DAUGHTER HAS
OTHER RESPONSIBILITIES.

239
00:14:34,666 --> 00:14:36,793
T'POL: THESE RELAYS
ARE CROSS-CIRCUITED.

240
00:14:36,835 --> 00:14:38,586
TUCKER: LIANA AND HER FATHER
REROUTED POWER

241
00:14:38,628 --> 00:14:40,004
WHERE THEY NEEDED IT.

242
00:14:40,046 --> 00:14:41,589
SEE HERE?

243
00:14:41,631 --> 00:14:44,843
THEY SHUNTED HELM CONTROL
TO AIRPONICS.

244
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:46,553
T'POL: EFFICIENT.

245
00:14:46,594 --> 00:14:48,638
BUT I'LL NEED TO RECONNECT
THE BRIDGE SYSTEMS.

246
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:50,264
TUCKER: I'LL ASK LIANA
TO GIVE YOU A HAND.

247
00:14:50,306 --> 00:14:51,641
T'POL: THAT'S NOT NECESSARY.

248
00:14:51,683 --> 00:14:53,017
TUCKER: IT'LL GO FASTER.

249
00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:54,602
T'POL: I CAN TAKE CARE OF IT.

250
00:14:54,644 --> 00:14:56,730
TUCKER: SHE KNOWS THE SHIP'S
SYSTEMS INSIDE AND OUT.

251
00:14:56,771 --> 00:15:00,441
SHE KEPT ME FROM GETTING FRIED
ON A LIVE PLASMA FEED.

252
00:15:00,483 --> 00:15:02,652
PERHAPS SHE CAN HELP YOU, THEN.

253
00:15:02,694 --> 00:15:04,904
WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

254
00:15:04,945 --> 00:15:06,656
BY THE WAY YOU KEEP
TALKING ABOUT HER,

255
00:15:06,698 --> 00:15:09,992
YOU OBVIOUSLY APPRECIATE
HER TECHNICAL EXPERTISE.

256
00:15:10,034 --> 00:15:11,911
SHE'S VERY COMPETENT.

257
00:15:11,952 --> 00:15:14,873
SO WAS THE FEMALE ENGINEER
ON THE XYRILLIAN SHIP.

258
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:17,250
TUCKER: YOU'RE NEVER GONNA
LET THAT GO, ARE YOU?

259
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:18,793
T'POL: I'M SIMPLY NOTING

260
00:15:18,835 --> 00:15:21,295
THAT THE LAST TIME YOU FOUND
SOMEONE THIS COMPETENT,

261
00:15:21,337 --> 00:15:23,840
YOU WOUND UP CARRYING HER CHILD.

262
00:15:25,341 --> 00:15:27,844
AM I INTERRUPTING?

263
00:15:27,886 --> 00:15:29,262
T'POL: NOT AT ALL.

264
00:15:29,303 --> 00:15:31,389
COMMANDER TUCKER AND I
WERE JUST DISCUSSING

265
00:15:31,431 --> 00:15:34,851
HIS PREVIOUS...
REPAIR EXPERIENCE.

266
00:15:34,893 --> 00:15:37,645
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT LIKE
SOMETHING TO EAT.

267
00:15:37,687 --> 00:15:39,689
T'POL: NO, THANK YOU.

268
00:15:39,731 --> 00:15:43,693
I'M GOING TO REMOVE THOSE
POWER SHUNTS ON THE BRIDGE.

269
00:15:53,411 --> 00:15:55,246
LIANA: ARE YOU HUNGRY?

270
00:15:55,288 --> 00:15:57,331
TUCKER: THANKS.

271
00:16:08,092 --> 00:16:10,136
MMM.

272
00:16:10,177 --> 00:16:11,387
IT'S DELICIOUS. WHAT IS IT?

273
00:16:11,429 --> 00:16:13,347
IT'S CALLED LORELLA.

274
00:16:13,389 --> 00:16:15,600
WE GROW IT
IN THE AIRPONICS BAY.

275
00:16:15,642 --> 00:16:17,101
NOTHING WILL TAKE ROOT
OUTSIDE.

276
00:16:17,143 --> 00:16:19,270
I'M NOT SURPRISED.

277
00:16:19,312 --> 00:16:21,856
IT'S AMAZING YOU WERE ABLE
TO SURVIVE OUT HERE.

278
00:16:27,194 --> 00:16:28,863
[ CHUCKLES ]

279
00:16:30,406 --> 00:16:33,242
WHY DO I FEEL LIKE
IT'S FEEDING TIME AT THE ZOO?

280
00:16:33,284 --> 00:16:35,870
OH. I DIDN'T MEAN TO BE RUDE.

281
00:16:35,912 --> 00:16:37,914
TUCKER: HMM. PLEASE.

282
00:16:37,956 --> 00:16:40,124
I WISH MORE WOMEN WOULD PAY
THAT MUCH ATTENTION TO ME.

283
00:16:40,166 --> 00:16:42,627
DO YOU KNOW A LOT OF WOMEN?

284
00:16:43,878 --> 00:16:48,424
WELL...NEARLY A THIRD
OF THE CREW IS FEMALE.

285
00:16:48,466 --> 00:16:52,219
WHAT ABOUT ON--
WHAT DID YOU CALL YOUR PLANET?

286
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:54,388
EARTH.

287
00:16:54,430 --> 00:16:57,266
I'VE GOT LADY FRIENDS
BACK THERE, BUT...

288
00:16:57,308 --> 00:16:59,853
NOBODY SPECIAL,
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU MEAN.

289
00:16:59,894 --> 00:17:02,021
NOT ANYMORE.

290
00:17:02,062 --> 00:17:04,649
WHAT ABOUT YOUR WORLD?

291
00:17:04,691 --> 00:17:06,567
KANTARE?

292
00:17:06,609 --> 00:17:08,736
WHAT ABOUT IT?

293
00:17:08,778 --> 00:17:10,697
WELL, AS SOON
AS WE GET YOUR ENGINES FIXED,

294
00:17:10,738 --> 00:17:13,616
YOU'LL BE GOING BACK,
SEEING YOUR FRIENDS.

295
00:17:13,658 --> 00:17:16,661
I BET YOU'RE LOOKING
FORWARD TO THAT.

296
00:17:19,163 --> 00:17:21,415
MAN: COMMANDER?

297
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:23,501
I HEAR YOU'VE BEEN
MAKING PROGRESS.

298
00:17:23,543 --> 00:17:25,879
UH, WE'RE GETTING THERE.

299
00:17:28,339 --> 00:17:29,883
THERE IS SOMETHING ELSE

300
00:17:29,924 --> 00:17:32,468
YOU MIGHT BE ABLE
TO HELP US WITH.

301
00:17:41,019 --> 00:17:42,603
T'POL: YOUR COMPUTER CORE?

302
00:17:42,645 --> 00:17:45,231
MAN: IT CONTROLS ALL THE SHIP'S
VITAL FUNCTIONS--

303
00:17:45,272 --> 00:17:49,068
ENVIRONMENTAL SYSTEMS,
MAIN POWER.

304
00:17:49,109 --> 00:17:52,071
YOU MIGHT SAY IT
KEEPS US ALIVE.

305
00:17:52,112 --> 00:17:54,073
T'POL: THESE ARE
OPTRONIC RELAYS.

306
00:17:54,114 --> 00:17:56,034
MAN: YES, AND THE SYSTEM'S
BEGINNING TO DEGRADE.

307
00:17:56,075 --> 00:17:57,660
IT COULD FAIL AT ANY TIME.

308
00:17:57,702 --> 00:18:01,497
I'VE WORKED
ON SOMETHING LIKE THIS...

309
00:18:01,539 --> 00:18:03,123
ON A XYRILLIAN SHIP.

310
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:04,751
MAN: THEN YOU CAN FIX IT?

311
00:18:04,792 --> 00:18:06,210
I CAN TRY.

312
00:18:06,252 --> 00:18:09,422
I'LL NEED SOME DIAGNOSTIC GEAR
FROM<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

313
00:18:11,465 --> 00:18:13,551
WHY DON'T YOU COME ALONG?

314
00:18:14,969 --> 00:18:17,096
I COULD BUY YOU LUNCH.

315
00:18:17,137 --> 00:18:18,598
MAN: THANK YOU, COMMANDER,

316
00:18:18,639 --> 00:18:20,182
BUT WE STILL HAVE
A LOT TO DO HERE.

317
00:18:20,224 --> 00:18:21,809
OH, YOU'VE BEEN MAROONED
FOR THREE YEARS.

318
00:18:21,851 --> 00:18:24,311
A CHANGE OF SCENERY FOR AN HOUR
OR TWO COULDN'T HURT.

319
00:18:24,353 --> 00:18:26,355
MAN: ANOTHER TIME.

320
00:18:26,397 --> 00:18:28,649
TUCKER: OK.

321
00:18:28,691 --> 00:18:31,986
I'LL BE BACK
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT.

322
00:18:36,074 --> 00:18:37,491
LIANA: WHY CAN'T I GO?

323
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:39,285
MAN: YOU KNOW WHY.

324
00:18:39,326 --> 00:18:41,037
LIANA: WHAT'S WRONG
WITH SEEING THEIR SHIP,

325
00:18:41,079 --> 00:18:42,580
MEETING SOME OF THEIR CREW?

326
00:18:42,622 --> 00:18:45,499
MAN: I THINK YOU'VE MET ENOUGH
OF THEIR CREW ALREADY.

327
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:49,003
LIANA: THESE ARE GOOD PEOPLE.
THEY WANT TO HELP US.

328
00:18:50,755 --> 00:18:53,424
I PROMISE NOT TO SAY ANYTHING.

329
00:18:55,468 --> 00:18:56,803
REED: HERE.

330
00:18:56,844 --> 00:18:59,346
THIS IS WHERE THEY SAY
THEIR ENGINES WERE HIT.

331
00:18:59,388 --> 00:19:01,432
ARCHER: THERE'S A LOT OF DAMAGE.

332
00:19:01,474 --> 00:19:03,601
REED: IMPACT DAMAGE, SIR.

333
00:19:03,643 --> 00:19:06,353
NO SCORCH MARKS.
NO MELTING.

334
00:19:06,395 --> 00:19:10,316
NO INDICATIONS
OF ANY WEAPONS FIRE.

335
00:19:10,357 --> 00:19:11,818
ARCHER: MAYBE THEY WERE HIT

336
00:19:11,859 --> 00:19:14,737
BY SOME KIND OF WEAPON
WE'RE NOT FAMILIAR WITH.

337
00:19:14,779 --> 00:19:17,406
REED: IT'S POSSIBLE.

338
00:19:17,448 --> 00:19:19,617
THEY ALSO SAY THEY HAVEN'T
SENT OUT A DISTRESS CALL

339
00:19:19,659 --> 00:19:22,202
BECAUSE IT'D GIVE AWAY
THEIR POSITION.

340
00:19:22,244 --> 00:19:24,371
ARCHER: YOU'RE NOT BUYING THAT,
EITHER?

341
00:19:24,413 --> 00:19:27,000
REED: THEY CRASHED
THREE YEARS AGO, SIR.

342
00:19:27,041 --> 00:19:29,919
WHOEVER ATTACKED THEM
HAS TO BE GONE BY NOW.

343
00:19:29,961 --> 00:19:33,006
WHY ARE THEY STILL HIDING?

344
00:19:33,047 --> 00:19:35,716
ARCHER: JUST BECAUSE
THEY'RE A LITTLE SKITTISH

345
00:19:35,758 --> 00:19:38,385
DOESN'T MEAN THEY'RE
UP TO SOMETHING.

346
00:19:38,427 --> 00:19:40,346
REED: THERE'S ALSO
THEIR AIRPONICS BAY.

347
00:19:40,387 --> 00:19:41,889
ARCHER: WHAT ABOUT IT?

348
00:19:41,931 --> 00:19:43,724
MAYWEATHER: IT'S NOT BIG ENOUGH
TO FEED ALL THE PEOPLE

349
00:19:43,766 --> 00:19:46,144
ON THAT SHIP, SIR;
NOT BY A LONG SHOT.

350
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:47,895
REED: HOW ARE THEY SURVIVING
DOWN THERE?

351
00:19:47,937 --> 00:19:49,897
IT DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

352
00:19:49,939 --> 00:19:52,025
ARCHER: DO WE STILL HAVE
THEIR DATA MODULE?

353
00:19:52,066 --> 00:19:53,985
MAYWEATHER: IT'S IN<i> </i>
<i>SHUTTLEPOD 1.</i>

354
00:19:54,027 --> 00:19:56,236
HAVE HOSHI DOWNLOAD IT.

355
00:19:56,278 --> 00:19:57,864
LET ME KNOW AS SOON
AS SHE HAS ANYTHING.

356
00:19:57,905 --> 00:20:00,158
MAYWEATHER: AYE, SIR.

357
00:20:05,579 --> 00:20:07,373
LIANA: HOW MANY PEOPLE
ARE ON<i> ENTERPRISE?</i>

358
00:20:07,414 --> 00:20:08,708
TUCKER: 83.

359
00:20:08,749 --> 00:20:10,793
-ALL HUMANS?
-MOSTLY.

360
00:20:10,835 --> 00:20:12,586
YOU MET T'POL--SHE'S VULCAN.

361
00:20:12,628 --> 00:20:15,255
AND DR. PHLOX IS
FROM A PLANET CALLED DENOBULA.

362
00:20:15,297 --> 00:20:17,133
-CAN I MEET HIM?
-ARE YOU KIDDING?

363
00:20:17,175 --> 00:20:19,886
I'D NEVER HEAR THE END OF IT
IF I DIDN'T INTRODUCE YOU.

364
00:20:19,927 --> 00:20:22,889
AND THERE'S PORTHOS,
CAPTAIN ARCHER'S DOG.

365
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:24,891
LIANA: DOG?

366
00:20:24,932 --> 00:20:27,727
TUCKER: OH, I GUESS
YOU DON'T HAVE A WORD FOR THAT.

367
00:20:27,768 --> 00:20:29,896
HE'S A MAMMAL.

368
00:20:29,937 --> 00:20:31,939
FOUR LEGS, BIG EARS,
KIND OF CUTE.

369
00:20:31,981 --> 00:20:33,315
LIANA: WHAT DOES HE DO?

370
00:20:33,357 --> 00:20:35,943
TUCKER: NOT MUCH.
HE'S THE CAPTAIN'S PET.

371
00:20:35,985 --> 00:20:38,196
LIANA: OF COURSE--HIS PET.
[ CHUCKLES ]

372
00:20:38,237 --> 00:20:40,198
I'VE NEVER SEEN A DOG BEFORE.

373
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:41,782
CAN WE SEE IT?

374
00:20:41,824 --> 00:20:43,242
TUCKER: WELL, I HOPE YOU'LL HAVE
SOME TIME LEFT FOR ME.

375
00:20:43,283 --> 00:20:44,618
LIANA: I DON'T KNOW.

376
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:46,037
IT SOUNDS LIKE I'M GOING
TO BE VERY BUSY.

377
00:20:46,079 --> 00:20:47,705
[ TUCKER CHUCKLES ]

378
00:20:47,747 --> 00:20:49,957
TUCKER: SO, TELL ME
ABOUT KANTARE.

379
00:20:49,999 --> 00:20:51,333
LIANA: IT'S BORING.

380
00:20:51,375 --> 00:20:53,377
I WANT TO HEAR ABOUT
THE PLACES YOU'VE BEEN.

381
00:20:53,419 --> 00:20:55,046
TUCKER: OUR MISSION'S REALLY
JUST GETTING STARTED.

382
00:20:55,088 --> 00:20:56,714
WE HAVEN'T BEEN
TO MANY PLANETS YET.

383
00:20:56,756 --> 00:20:58,507
LIANA: WHERE ARE YOU GOING NEXT?

384
00:20:58,549 --> 00:21:00,218
TUCKER: NO IDEA.

385
00:21:00,259 --> 00:21:02,595
THAT'S THE FUN PART.

386
00:21:02,636 --> 00:21:05,556
LIANA: WHICH PLANET
WAS YOUR FAVORITE?

387
00:21:05,598 --> 00:21:08,601
TUCKER: IF I HAD TO CHOOSE
RIGHT NOW...

388
00:21:08,642 --> 00:21:10,019
I'D SAY THIS ONE.

389
00:21:10,061 --> 00:21:11,270
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

390
00:21:11,311 --> 00:21:13,522
Archer: Archer
to Commander Tucker.

391
00:21:13,564 --> 00:21:15,191
GO AHEAD.

392
00:21:15,233 --> 00:21:16,943
Archer: Could you come
to my ready room?

393
00:21:16,984 --> 00:21:18,736
ON MY WAY. BILLY?

394
00:21:18,778 --> 00:21:21,280
COULD YOU CONTINUE
THIS LADY'S TOUR?

395
00:21:21,321 --> 00:21:22,573
I STILL OWE YOU LUNCH.

396
00:21:22,615 --> 00:21:25,243
I'LL MEET YOU IN THE MESS HALL.

397
00:21:29,872 --> 00:21:33,375
I HEAR YOU'VE BEEN SPENDING
A LOT OF TIME WITH LIANA.

398
00:21:33,417 --> 00:21:36,254
TUCKER: DID T'POL SAY SOMETHING?

399
00:21:36,295 --> 00:21:40,133
SIR, I SWEAR I'VE BEEN NOTHING
BUT A PERFECT GENTLEMAN.

400
00:21:40,174 --> 00:21:41,842
ARCHER: I'M SURE YOU HAVE, TRIP.

401
00:21:41,884 --> 00:21:45,596
THIS DOESN'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO DO WITH THAT.

402
00:21:45,638 --> 00:21:47,265
TUCKER: OH.

403
00:21:47,306 --> 00:21:48,682
ARCHER: WE WERE WONDERING

404
00:21:48,724 --> 00:21:51,060
IF YOU'D NOTICED ANY STRANGE
BEHAVIOR FROM HER

405
00:21:51,102 --> 00:21:53,146
OR ANY OF THE OTHERS.

406
00:21:53,187 --> 00:21:54,897
TUCKER: STRANGE BEHAVIOR?

407
00:21:54,939 --> 00:21:56,732
WHAT'S GOING ON?

408
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:01,403
HOSHI TRANSLATED THE DATA MODULE
WE FOUND ON THEIR SHIP.

409
00:22:01,445 --> 00:22:03,156
WE WERE ABLE
TO RECONSTRUCT WHAT HAPPENED

410
00:22:03,197 --> 00:22:04,657
RIGHT BEFORE THEY CRASHED.

411
00:22:04,698 --> 00:22:06,325
THEY ALREADY TOLD US
WHAT HAPPENED.

412
00:22:06,366 --> 00:22:09,078
ACCORDING TO THIS...

413
00:22:09,120 --> 00:22:11,747
THEY WEREN'T ATTACKED.

414
00:22:11,789 --> 00:22:14,041
THERE WAS AN ACCIDENT ONBOARD.

415
00:22:14,083 --> 00:22:15,918
WHAT KIND OF AN ACCIDENT?

416
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:18,045
REED: THERE ARE SOME GAPS
IN THE DATA,

417
00:22:18,087 --> 00:22:21,215
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE SOME KIND
OF CATASTROPHIC MALFUNCTION.

418
00:22:21,257 --> 00:22:23,342
THERE WAS
A MASSIVE DEPRESSURIZATION

419
00:22:23,383 --> 00:22:25,343
WHEN THE SHIP WENT DOWN.

420
00:22:25,385 --> 00:22:28,472
TUCKER: MAYBE THAT DATA MODULE
WAS DAMAGED DURING THE CRASH.

421
00:22:28,514 --> 00:22:32,268
IT'S NOT JUST THE DATA MODULE.

422
00:22:32,310 --> 00:22:34,394
REED: WHEN THEIR STORY
DIDN'T CHECK OUT,

423
00:22:34,436 --> 00:22:37,606
THE CAPTAIN ASKED ME TO RUN SOME
DETAILED SCANS OF THE SHIP.

424
00:22:37,648 --> 00:22:41,694
ACCORDING TO THE OXIDATION RATE
IN THE HULL PLATING...

425
00:22:41,735 --> 00:22:43,612
THAT SHIP'S BEEN
SITTING DOWN THERE

426
00:22:43,654 --> 00:22:45,572
A LOT LONGER THAN THREE YEARS.

427
00:22:45,614 --> 00:22:49,202
IT WENT DOWN
NEARLY 22 YEARS AGO, TRIP.

428
00:22:49,243 --> 00:22:52,412
TUCKER: THAT DOESN'T MAKE
ANY SENSE.

429
00:22:52,454 --> 00:22:55,291
REED: CHECK THE SCANS YOURSELF.

430
00:22:57,043 --> 00:22:59,545
TUCKER: WHY WOULDN'T LIANA
HAVE TOLD ME?

431
00:22:59,586 --> 00:23:01,088
REED: THE DATA ALSO SHOWS

432
00:23:01,130 --> 00:23:03,590
THAT THEY LAUNCHED
A NUMBER OF ESCAPE PODS

433
00:23:03,632 --> 00:23:05,343
JUST BEFORE THE CRASH.

434
00:23:05,383 --> 00:23:07,303
MALCOLM FOUND ONE.

435
00:23:07,345 --> 00:23:09,680
IT WAS STILL IN ORBIT.

436
00:23:09,722 --> 00:23:12,225
WE'RE BRINGING IT ONBOARD.

437
00:23:14,643 --> 00:23:17,855
PHLOX: THIS IS OBVIOUSLY
SOMEONE'S FINAL RESTING PLACE.

438
00:23:17,897 --> 00:23:20,482
WHAT DO YOU EXPECT TO ACCOMPLISH
BY OPENING IT?

439
00:23:20,524 --> 00:23:23,194
ARCHER: I'M NOT QUITE SURE.

440
00:23:39,085 --> 00:23:42,420
PHLOX: I DON'T BELIEVE
YOU'LL BE NEEDING MY SERVICES.

441
00:23:44,090 --> 00:23:46,217
TUCKER: IT'S SHILAT, CAPTAIN.

442
00:23:46,259 --> 00:23:49,678
I SAW HIM ON THEIR SHIP
AN HOUR AGO...

443
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:52,265
ALIVE.

444
00:24:01,857 --> 00:24:04,568
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

445
00:24:38,227 --> 00:24:40,104
TUCKER: VANILLA, HUH?

446
00:24:40,146 --> 00:24:41,479
LIANA: THERE ARE
DIFFERENT KINDS?

447
00:24:41,521 --> 00:24:43,857
OH, HUNDREDS.

448
00:24:43,899 --> 00:24:45,609
I LIKE ROCKY ROAD.

449
00:24:45,651 --> 00:24:47,569
THAT SOUNDS TERRIBLE.

450
00:24:47,611 --> 00:24:49,071
WHY DO THEY CALL IT THAT?

451
00:24:49,113 --> 00:24:51,489
I NEVER REALLY
THOUGHT ABOUT IT.

452
00:24:51,531 --> 00:24:54,534
I GUESS BECAUSE
IT'S GOT NUTS IN IT.

453
00:24:54,576 --> 00:24:56,036
IT'S ALSO GOT MARSHMALLOWS,

454
00:24:56,078 --> 00:24:57,579
BUT I DON'T THINK
THAT'S GOT ANYTHING TO DO

455
00:24:57,621 --> 00:24:58,747
WITH THE NAME.

456
00:24:58,789 --> 00:24:59,832
MARSHMALLOWS?

457
00:24:59,873 --> 00:25:01,959
THEY'RE LITTLE, UM...

458
00:25:02,001 --> 00:25:05,463
UH, THEY'RE MADE OF SUGAR,
MOSTLY.

459
00:25:05,503 --> 00:25:07,340
YOU KNOW, I'M NOT SURE
WHAT THEY ARE.

460
00:25:07,381 --> 00:25:09,133
[ CHUCKLING ]

461
00:25:09,175 --> 00:25:12,219
ANYWAY, DID YOU ENJOY THE TOUR?

462
00:25:12,261 --> 00:25:13,720
OH, VERY MUCH.

463
00:25:13,762 --> 00:25:15,555
I THINK SICK BAY
WAS MY FAVORITE.

464
00:25:15,597 --> 00:25:17,433
DR. PHLOX LET ME FEED HIS BAT.

465
00:25:17,475 --> 00:25:18,976
OOH.

466
00:25:19,018 --> 00:25:21,020
LIANA: HE ALSO
ASKED ME TO LUNCH.

467
00:25:21,061 --> 00:25:23,063
HAD I KNOWN YOU WERE GONNA
BE GONE SO LONG...

468
00:25:23,105 --> 00:25:24,398
I'M SORRY.

469
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:28,819
UM...SOMETHING IMPORTANT
CAME UP.

470
00:25:28,861 --> 00:25:31,738
WHAT'S WRONG?

471
00:25:31,780 --> 00:25:35,284
LIANA, HOW LONG
HAVE YOU BEEN ON THIS PLANET?

472
00:25:35,326 --> 00:25:38,329
CAPTAIN KUULAN TOLD YOU.

473
00:25:38,371 --> 00:25:39,955
I WANT YOU TO TELL ME.

474
00:25:39,997 --> 00:25:41,748
WHY?

475
00:25:41,790 --> 00:25:46,003
BECAUSE OUR SCANS SHOW
YOUR SHIP CRASHED 22 YEARS AGO.

476
00:25:46,045 --> 00:25:47,713
WELL, YOUR SCANS MUST BE WRONG.

477
00:25:47,754 --> 00:25:49,340
TUCKER: THAT'S WHAT I TOLD
CAPTAIN ARCHER.

478
00:25:49,382 --> 00:25:53,844
I SAID THERE WASN'T ANY REASON
FOR YOU TO LIE TO US.

479
00:25:53,886 --> 00:25:55,888
IS THERE?

480
00:26:02,811 --> 00:26:05,523
WE FOUND
ONE OF YOUR ESCAPE PODS.

481
00:26:06,690 --> 00:26:07,941
I THINK I SHOULD GO NOW.

482
00:26:07,983 --> 00:26:09,567
-LIANA?
-TAKE ME BACK.

483
00:26:09,609 --> 00:26:12,321
TUCKER: THERE WAS A BODY IN IT,
BEEN DEAD FOR A LONG TIME.

484
00:26:12,363 --> 00:26:14,698
IT WAS SHILAT.

485
00:26:14,740 --> 00:26:15,782
CAN YOU EXPLAIN THAT TO ME?

486
00:26:15,824 --> 00:26:16,950
LIANA: I CAN'T.

487
00:26:16,992 --> 00:26:18,327
TUCKER: TELL ME WHAT'S GOING ON.

488
00:26:18,369 --> 00:26:20,496
LIANA: I'M SORRY, BUT I CAN'T.

489
00:26:20,538 --> 00:26:23,541
PLEASE TAKE ME HOME.

490
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:04,831
SHILAT: DO YOU NEED SOME HELP?

491
00:27:04,873 --> 00:27:06,417
T'POL: NOT AT ALL.

492
00:27:06,459 --> 00:27:09,128
SHILAT: I THOUGHT YOU WERE
REPAIRING THE OPTRONIC RELAYS.

493
00:27:09,169 --> 00:27:11,505
I'VE DONE AS MUCH
AS I CAN DO FOR NOW.

494
00:27:11,547 --> 00:27:14,841
I NEED TO RETURN TO<i> ENTERPRISE</i> 
TO ANALYZE THE DATA.

495
00:27:14,883 --> 00:27:17,470
IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME...

496
00:27:20,097 --> 00:27:21,557
DO YOU NEED SOME HELP?

497
00:27:21,599 --> 00:27:24,017
I NEED TO CONTACT MY SHIP.

498
00:27:24,059 --> 00:27:26,145
BECAUSE OF WHAT YOU FOUND?

499
00:27:26,186 --> 00:27:28,314
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

500
00:27:28,355 --> 00:27:31,900
YOU WERE LOOKING
WHERE YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE.

501
00:27:48,626 --> 00:27:50,169
ARCHER: FIND T'POL.

502
00:27:50,210 --> 00:27:51,878
I'M GONNA GO
TALK TO THE CAPTAIN.

503
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:53,339
REED: I THINK IT WOULD BE BETTER
IF WE STAYED TOGETHER, SIR.

504
00:27:53,380 --> 00:27:54,798
LIANA: YOU DON'T HAVE
TO DO THIS.

505
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:56,300
YOU'RE NOT IN ANY DANGER HERE.

506
00:27:56,342 --> 00:27:57,593
ARCHER: THAT WOULD BE
EASIER TO BELIEVE

507
00:27:57,635 --> 00:27:59,345
IF YOU WEREN'T HIDING
THINGS FROM US.

508
00:27:59,386 --> 00:28:01,888
LIANA: CAN'T YOU JUST
FIX OUR SYSTEMS AND GO?

509
00:28:01,930 --> 00:28:04,224
TUCKER: IS THAT WHAT
YOU REALLY WANT?

510
00:28:04,266 --> 00:28:07,853
HOW OLD WERE YOU WHEN
YOUR SHIP CRASHED--5, 6?

511
00:28:07,894 --> 00:28:10,189
DO YOU EVEN REMEMBER
WHAT YOUR HOME LOOKS LIKE?

512
00:28:10,230 --> 00:28:12,941
LIANA: THIS IS MY HOME.

513
00:28:12,983 --> 00:28:14,860
MAN: LIANA?

514
00:28:15,986 --> 00:28:18,738
LIANA: I DIDN'T
TELL THEM ANYTHING.

515
00:28:18,780 --> 00:28:20,824
ARCHER: NO, SHE DIDN'T.

516
00:28:20,866 --> 00:28:22,409
BUT IF YOU WANT
ANY MORE HELP FROM US,

517
00:28:22,451 --> 00:28:24,119
WE'RE GONNA NEED SOME ANSWERS.

518
00:28:24,161 --> 00:28:27,039
SHILAT: WE DON'T OWE YOU
ANSWERS.

519
00:28:27,080 --> 00:28:29,124
KUULAN: TAKE THEIR WEAPONS.

520
00:28:32,378 --> 00:28:33,962
PLEASE, JUST LET THEM LEAVE.

521
00:28:34,004 --> 00:28:35,839
THAT'S WHAT YOU WANTED
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

522
00:28:35,881 --> 00:28:38,175
KUULAN: WHEN THE REPAIRS
ARE COMPLETED.

523
00:28:42,638 --> 00:28:45,599
MAKE HIM STOP.
HE'LL LISTEN TO YOU.

524
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:49,436
KUULAN: GO BACK TO YOUR SHIP.

525
00:28:49,478 --> 00:28:51,188
ARCHER: NOT WITHOUT MY OFFICERS.

526
00:28:51,230 --> 00:28:53,857
KUULAN: THIS ISN'T
A NEGOTIATION.

527
00:29:04,368 --> 00:29:06,412
LIANA?

528
00:29:15,045 --> 00:29:16,547
SHILAT: GET TO WORK.

529
00:29:16,589 --> 00:29:18,632
WHERE'S T'POL?

530
00:29:18,674 --> 00:29:21,218
-DON'T WORRY ABOUT HER.
-I'M GONNA NEED HER HELP.

531
00:29:21,260 --> 00:29:22,802
MAN: YOU CAN DO IT ON YOUR OWN.

532
00:29:22,844 --> 00:29:25,055
I'M NOT DOING A THING
UNTIL I SEE HER.

533
00:29:25,097 --> 00:29:28,392
MAN: DO AS I SAY,
OR YOU'LL NEVER SEE HER.

534
00:29:28,434 --> 00:29:31,311
WHAT'S SO IMPORTANT
ABOUT THIS THING?

535
00:29:31,353 --> 00:29:33,313
YOU'D REALLY KILL US
TO KEEP IT RUNNING?

536
00:29:33,355 --> 00:29:35,941
YOU WOULDN'T UNDERSTAND.

537
00:29:35,982 --> 00:29:37,943
I DON'T CARE
WHAT YOUR BIG SECRET IS.

538
00:29:37,984 --> 00:29:40,946
IT DOESN'T MATTER IF YOU'VE
BEEN HERE 3 YEARS OR 30.

539
00:29:40,987 --> 00:29:43,823
BUT YOU GOT TO THINK
ABOUT LIANA.

540
00:29:43,865 --> 00:29:46,910
WE CAN HELP YOU
TAKE HER HOME.

541
00:29:46,952 --> 00:29:49,246
MAN: JUST FIX THOSE RELAYS.

542
00:29:49,288 --> 00:29:52,207
YOU GOT A LOT TO LEARN
ABOUT MAKING FRIENDS.

543
00:29:54,752 --> 00:29:58,380
I'VE MADE
ALL THE FRIENDS I NEED.

544
00:30:02,760 --> 00:30:05,220
LIANA: I'M SICK OF HEARING
THAT HE'S DOING THIS FOR ME.

545
00:30:05,262 --> 00:30:06,930
I DON'T BELIEVE IT ANYMORE.

546
00:30:06,972 --> 00:30:09,099
WOMAN: I WOULDN'T BE ALIVE
IF IT WASN'T FOR YOUR FATHER.

547
00:30:09,141 --> 00:30:10,934
LIANA: HE STILL SHOULD'VE
TOLD THEM THE TRUTH.

548
00:30:10,976 --> 00:30:12,394
WOMAN: YOU KNOW
HE CAN'T DO THAT.

549
00:30:12,436 --> 00:30:13,853
LIANA: HE CAN DO
WHATEVER HE WANTS.

550
00:30:13,895 --> 00:30:15,897
HE'S NOT LIKE YOU.

551
00:30:17,107 --> 00:30:18,734
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE
GONE TO THEIR SHIP.

552
00:30:18,776 --> 00:30:20,860
YOU THINK THIS IS MY FAULT?

553
00:30:20,902 --> 00:30:22,655
WOMAN: I SAW THE WAY YOU LOOKED
AT THEIR ENGINEER.

554
00:30:22,696 --> 00:30:25,157
ARE YOU SURE YOU
DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING?

555
00:30:25,198 --> 00:30:27,660
NO, I DIDN'T.

556
00:30:27,701 --> 00:30:31,789
THEY'LL BE GONE SOON, AND
EVERYTHING WILL BE FINE AGAIN.

557
00:30:39,171 --> 00:30:41,047
ARCHER: WE'LL SET
THE SHUTTLE DOWN

558
00:30:41,089 --> 00:30:43,008
IN THE FOOTHILLS
SOUTH OF THEIR SHIP.

559
00:30:43,049 --> 00:30:44,677
MAYWEATHER: WON'T THEY
PICK US UP ON SENSORS?

560
00:30:44,718 --> 00:30:45,927
THEIR DAMPENING FIELD

561
00:30:45,969 --> 00:30:47,387
SHOULD LEAVE THEM
AS BLIND AS WE ARE.

562
00:30:47,429 --> 00:30:48,930
REED: UNFORTUNATELY,
THAT RULES OUT

563
00:30:48,972 --> 00:30:50,683
USING THE TRANSPORTER AS WELL.

564
00:30:50,724 --> 00:30:52,643
WE'LL GO IN THROUGH
THEIR ESCAPE-POD PORTS.

565
00:30:52,685 --> 00:30:54,311
THAT SHOULD PUT US
NEAR ENGINEERING

566
00:30:54,353 --> 00:30:55,937
AND THEIR COMPUTER ROOM.

567
00:30:55,979 --> 00:30:59,274
AND, WITH A BIT OF LUCK,
NEAR T'POL AND COMMANDER TUCKER.

568
00:31:03,028 --> 00:31:06,031
THAT'S A PRETTY NEAT TRICK.

569
00:31:06,072 --> 00:31:09,451
HERE YOU ARE WATCHING ME
WITH A GUN IN YOUR HAND,

570
00:31:09,493 --> 00:31:14,247
WHILE AT THE SAME TIME,
YOUR CORPSE IS UP ON<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

571
00:31:14,289 --> 00:31:17,292
WHAT DO YOU DO FOR AN ENCORE?

572
00:31:20,546 --> 00:31:22,339
WOULD YOU WAIT OUTSIDE?

573
00:31:22,381 --> 00:31:24,383
I'M NOT SUPPOSED TO LEAVE HIM.

574
00:31:24,424 --> 00:31:26,885
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

575
00:31:38,647 --> 00:31:41,107
THEY DO WHAT I ASK THEM TO.

576
00:31:41,149 --> 00:31:43,694
TUCKER: THEN WHY DON'T YOU
ASK THEM TO LET ME GO?

577
00:31:43,736 --> 00:31:46,112
LIANA: I WISH I COULD.

578
00:31:46,154 --> 00:31:48,240
TUCKER: MAYBE YOU CAN TELL ME
HOW I'M BEING GUARDED

579
00:31:48,281 --> 00:31:50,367
BY A DEAD MAN.

580
00:31:52,202 --> 00:31:54,913
LIANA: DO YOU THINK
IT'S POSSIBLE TO TELL A LIE

581
00:31:54,954 --> 00:31:59,959
SO MANY TIMES THAT YOU BEGIN
TO BELIEVE IT'S THE TRUTH?

582
00:32:02,379 --> 00:32:05,591
YOU CAN.

583
00:32:05,632 --> 00:32:10,095
I NEVER REALLY UNDERSTOOD THAT
UNTIL YOU CAME.

584
00:32:11,889 --> 00:32:15,642
REMEMBER WHEN YOU SAID
YOU THOUGHT WE WERE GHOSTS?

585
00:32:18,478 --> 00:32:22,065
IN A WAY...YOU WERE RIGHT.

586
00:32:26,570 --> 00:32:29,489
ARCHER: WORK YOUR WAY
DOWN THE PORT SIDE.

587
00:32:29,531 --> 00:32:32,826
COM US IF YOU FIND T'POL,
AND BE CAREFUL.

588
00:32:32,868 --> 00:32:35,328
MAYWEATHER: AYE, SIR.

589
00:32:59,436 --> 00:33:00,896
REED: UGH!

590
00:33:02,063 --> 00:33:04,858
[ REED GROANS ]

591
00:33:13,659 --> 00:33:16,829
THAT'S WHY YOUR FATHER
NEEDS TO KEEP THIS RUNNING.

592
00:33:16,870 --> 00:33:18,747
LIANA: YES.

593
00:33:18,789 --> 00:33:20,499
[ WEAPONS FIRE ]

594
00:33:20,540 --> 00:33:22,960
TUCKER: YOU CAN STOP THIS.

595
00:33:25,545 --> 00:33:28,548
REED: OH, OH, GOD.

596
00:33:32,051 --> 00:33:33,804
[ GROANING ]

597
00:33:33,846 --> 00:33:35,180
ARCHER: YOU ALL RIGHT?

598
00:33:35,221 --> 00:33:36,849
REED: YEAH.
WHERE DID HE COME FROM?

599
00:33:36,890 --> 00:33:38,809
ARCHER: GOOD QUESTION.

600
00:33:43,438 --> 00:33:45,983
MAN: YOU HAVE TO GET THEM
OFF THE SHIP.

601
00:33:56,910 --> 00:33:58,537
TUCKER: LIANA, PLEASE.

602
00:33:58,578 --> 00:34:01,665
IF YOU DON'T,
MY FRIENDS COULD DIE.

603
00:34:01,707 --> 00:34:04,292
PLEASE.

604
00:34:08,005 --> 00:34:10,507
REED: OHH!

605
00:34:10,549 --> 00:34:13,134
[ GRUNTING ]

606
00:35:05,228 --> 00:35:07,355
ARCHER: WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOUR CREW?

607
00:35:07,397 --> 00:35:10,400
MAN: THEY'RE GONE, CAPTAIN.
ISN'T IT OBVIOUS?

608
00:35:10,442 --> 00:35:12,235
ARCHER: YOUR<i> REAL</i> CREW.

609
00:35:12,277 --> 00:35:13,779
MAN: AH.

610
00:35:13,820 --> 00:35:16,615
THEY DIDN'T SEEM REAL TO YOU?

611
00:35:16,656 --> 00:35:18,742
I CREATED THEM.

612
00:35:18,784 --> 00:35:20,535
WASN'T EASY.

613
00:35:20,577 --> 00:35:22,829
TOOK TIME.

614
00:35:22,871 --> 00:35:25,040
YOU COULD TOUCH THEM.

615
00:35:25,082 --> 00:35:28,585
THEY COULD MAKE YOU LAUGH,
SURPRISE YOU.

616
00:35:28,627 --> 00:35:30,879
THEY WERE HOLOGRAMS.

617
00:35:32,464 --> 00:35:36,718
MAN: THEY WERE OUR FRIENDS,
OUR FAMILY, FOR OVER 20 YEARS.

618
00:35:36,760 --> 00:35:39,096
LIANA: THEY'RE THE ONLY PEOPLE
I'VE EVER KNOWN

619
00:35:39,137 --> 00:35:43,349
BESIDES MY FATHER,
UNTIL YOU CAME.

620
00:35:43,391 --> 00:35:45,351
ARCHER: BUT THE ONES
YOU BASED THEM ON--

621
00:35:45,393 --> 00:35:48,688
THE CREW OF THIS SHIP--
WHERE ARE THEY?

622
00:35:48,730 --> 00:35:52,025
MAN: I BURIED THEM
OUT IN THE HILLS--

623
00:35:52,067 --> 00:35:56,071
THE ONES I COULD FIND
AFTER THE CRASH.

624
00:35:56,113 --> 00:35:58,657
I KILLED THEM,
SO I BURIED THEM.

625
00:35:58,698 --> 00:36:00,075
LIANA: IT ISN'T TRUE.

626
00:36:00,117 --> 00:36:01,534
MAN: YOU DON'T REMEMBER.

627
00:36:01,576 --> 00:36:04,621
YOU WERE A CHILD.

628
00:36:04,663 --> 00:36:08,249
WE WERE ON OUR WAY HOME,
JUST LIKE KUULAN TOLD YOU,

629
00:36:08,291 --> 00:36:10,585
BUT WE WEREN'T ATTACKED.

630
00:36:10,627 --> 00:36:12,295
IT WAS AN ION STORM.

631
00:36:12,337 --> 00:36:14,506
IT OVERLOADED
OUR PLASMA CONDUITS.

632
00:36:14,547 --> 00:36:16,382
I WAS THE CHIEF ENGINEER

633
00:36:16,424 --> 00:36:19,594
AND IT WAS MY RESPONSIBILITY
TO START REPAIRS.

634
00:36:19,636 --> 00:36:23,222
BUT IT WAS WORSE THAN I THOUGHT.

635
00:36:23,264 --> 00:36:26,810
LEAKING PLASMA BURNED
THROUGH THE HULL.

636
00:36:26,852 --> 00:36:28,436
WE WERE LOSING ATMOSPHERE,

637
00:36:28,478 --> 00:36:31,773
SO CAPTAIN KUULAN SET
A COURSE FOR THIS PLANET.

638
00:36:31,815 --> 00:36:33,650
ARCHER: SOUNDS LIKE YOU DID
EVERYTHING YOU COULD

639
00:36:33,692 --> 00:36:35,068
TO SAVE THE SHIP.

640
00:36:35,110 --> 00:36:36,277
[ MAN SCOFFS ]

641
00:36:36,319 --> 00:36:38,446
THEY'RE ALL DEAD.

642
00:36:38,488 --> 00:36:41,240
APPARENTLY, I DIDN'T DO ENOUGH.

643
00:36:41,282 --> 00:36:42,951
LIANA: THEY DIED BECAUSE OF ME.

644
00:36:42,993 --> 00:36:44,452
MAN: NO!

645
00:36:44,494 --> 00:36:46,746
IT WAS MY DECISION.

646
00:36:46,788 --> 00:36:50,333
SHE WAS IN OUR QUARTERS
ON THE LOWEST DECK.

647
00:36:50,375 --> 00:36:54,046
I KNEW SHE'D NEVER SURVIVE
A CRASH LANDING DOWN THERE,

648
00:36:54,087 --> 00:36:55,881
SO I WENT TO GET HER.

649
00:36:55,922 --> 00:36:59,009
ARCHER: ANY FATHER WOULD HAVE
DONE THE SAME THING.

650
00:36:59,051 --> 00:37:02,220
I LEFT MY STATION.

651
00:37:02,261 --> 00:37:05,974
THE PLASMA LEAK GREW.
THERE WAS AN EXPLOSION.

652
00:37:06,016 --> 00:37:08,935
HALF THE CREW DIED INSTANTLY...

653
00:37:08,977 --> 00:37:11,730
INCLUDING MY WIFE.

654
00:37:11,771 --> 00:37:16,526
A FEW MADE IT
TO THE ESCAPE PODS, BUT...

655
00:37:18,611 --> 00:37:22,032
ARCHER: I...CAN'T IMAGINE

656
00:37:22,074 --> 00:37:25,994
WHAT MAKING THAT DECISION
MUST HAVE BEEN LIKE,

657
00:37:26,036 --> 00:37:27,996
BUT IT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

658
00:37:28,038 --> 00:37:30,707
YOU NEED TO CONSIDER
YOUR DAUGHTER NOW.

659
00:37:30,749 --> 00:37:34,377
MAN: WHY DO YOU THINK
I DID THIS?

660
00:37:34,419 --> 00:37:37,672
TO RETREAT INTO SOME FANTASY,
PRETEND IT NEVER HAPPENED?

661
00:37:37,714 --> 00:37:41,551
FOR TWO YEARS, I TRIED
TO REPAIR OUR SHIP,

662
00:37:41,593 --> 00:37:46,890
AND I WATCHED MY DAUGHTER
GROW UP ALONE.

663
00:37:46,932 --> 00:37:49,684
SO I DECIDED
TO BRING THEM BACK--

664
00:37:49,726 --> 00:37:55,356
HER MOTHER FIRST, THEN
CAPTAIN KUULAN AND THE OTHERS.

665
00:37:55,398 --> 00:38:00,237
I DID EVERYTHING I COULD
TO MAKE IT LIKE IT WAS FOR HER.

666
00:38:00,278 --> 00:38:02,321
SHE DESERVES MORE.

667
00:38:03,949 --> 00:38:06,576
MAN: I'VE GIVEN HER
EVERYTHING SHE NEEDS.

668
00:38:06,618 --> 00:38:08,036
AND WHEN YOU'RE GONE?

669
00:38:08,078 --> 00:38:09,412
LIANA: TRIP, PLEASE.

670
00:38:09,454 --> 00:38:11,998
ARE YOU GONNA LET HER
BURY YOU OUT IN THE HILLS

671
00:38:12,040 --> 00:38:14,500
AND LIVE THE REST
OF HER LIFE WITH THESE...

672
00:38:14,542 --> 00:38:16,502
PEOPLE YOU CREATED?

673
00:38:16,544 --> 00:38:19,589
WHAT IF THE RELAYS
BURN OUT AGAIN?

674
00:38:19,631 --> 00:38:21,091
THEN SHE'LL REALLY BE ALONE.

675
00:38:21,133 --> 00:38:24,469
MAN: SHE'S MY DAUGHTER.
IT'S NOT YOUR CONCERN.

676
00:38:25,929 --> 00:38:28,431
WHAT IF SHE GETS HURT?

677
00:38:28,473 --> 00:38:30,683
WHAT DO YOU DO THEN?

678
00:38:30,725 --> 00:38:34,062
PROGRAM A...HOLOGRAPHIC DOCTOR?

679
00:38:34,104 --> 00:38:36,273
MAN: WE'VE SURVIVED HERE
SUCCESSFULLY.

680
00:38:36,314 --> 00:38:39,192
MAYBE YOU HAVE.

681
00:38:39,234 --> 00:38:41,527
ASK LIANA HOW SHE FEELS.

682
00:38:41,569 --> 00:38:45,073
ASK HER IF JUST SURVIVING
IS ENOUGH.

683
00:38:51,079 --> 00:38:53,123
ARCHER: YOU ALL RIGHT?

684
00:38:56,251 --> 00:38:58,461
WE'LL FINISH WORKING ON
YOUR HOLOGRAPHIC SYSTEMS,

685
00:38:58,503 --> 00:39:00,797
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT.

686
00:39:00,839 --> 00:39:02,340
BUT YOU SHOULD BE SURE

687
00:39:02,381 --> 00:39:04,425
THAT'S ALL THE HELP
YOU NEED FROM US.

688
00:39:04,467 --> 00:39:08,346
IT MAY BE A LONG TIME BEFORE
ANYONE COMES BY HERE AGAIN.

689
00:39:16,229 --> 00:39:17,396
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

690
00:39:17,438 --> 00:39:19,440
COME IN.

691
00:39:27,615 --> 00:39:29,242
WELCOME ABOARD.

692
00:39:29,284 --> 00:39:31,661
THANK YOU, CAPTAIN.

693
00:39:35,123 --> 00:39:37,876
YOU HAVE A BEAUTIFUL SHIP.

694
00:39:37,917 --> 00:39:41,254
THANKS.
WE'RE PRETTY PROUD OF HER.

695
00:39:44,465 --> 00:39:45,800
MAY I SIT?

696
00:39:45,842 --> 00:39:48,178
ARCHER: OF COURSE.

697
00:39:49,804 --> 00:39:52,265
[ SIGHS ]

698
00:39:54,475 --> 00:39:56,561
I HAVEN'T BEEN IN SPACE
FOR A LONG TIME.

699
00:39:56,602 --> 00:39:59,981
IT FEELS STRANGE.

700
00:40:00,023 --> 00:40:04,069
GOOD, JUST A BIT STRANGE.

701
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:07,446
CAN I GET YOU SOMETHING?

702
00:40:07,488 --> 00:40:08,614
SOME TEA?

703
00:40:08,656 --> 00:40:10,367
MAN: I'M FINE.

704
00:40:12,410 --> 00:40:14,495
NO, I'M NOT.

705
00:40:16,331 --> 00:40:20,252
YOUR ENGINEER
IS A VERY PLAIN-SPOKEN MAN.

706
00:40:20,293 --> 00:40:24,214
THAT'S ONE WAY OF PUTTING IT.

707
00:40:29,094 --> 00:40:33,598
I'VE NEVER KEPT SECRETS
FROM MY DAUGHTER.

708
00:40:33,639 --> 00:40:36,184
SHE KNOWS THERE'S MORE TO SEE

709
00:40:36,226 --> 00:40:39,729
BEYOND OUR LITTLE OASIS.

710
00:40:39,771 --> 00:40:44,150
BUT SHE'S NEVER TALKED
ABOUT LEAVING...

711
00:40:44,192 --> 00:40:46,652
NOT ONCE.

712
00:40:46,694 --> 00:40:48,780
NOW YOUR ENGINEER THINKS
WE SHOULD JUST

713
00:40:48,821 --> 00:40:52,200
PACK UP AND GO.

714
00:40:52,242 --> 00:40:54,119
[ SIGHS ]

715
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:57,455
22 YEARS, CAPTAIN.

716
00:40:57,496 --> 00:40:59,958
I'VE LIVED HERE FOR 22 YEARS.

717
00:40:59,999 --> 00:41:01,376
NOW, THAT SHIP DOWN THERE

718
00:41:01,418 --> 00:41:06,089
MAY SEEM LIKE NOTHING MORE
THAN SPARE PARTS TO YOU,

719
00:41:06,131 --> 00:41:10,260
BUT TO ME, IT'S HOME.

720
00:41:10,302 --> 00:41:12,887
I DON'T WANT TO LEAVE.

721
00:41:12,929 --> 00:41:15,556
I AM HAPPY HERE.

722
00:41:18,059 --> 00:41:20,228
COMFORTABLE.

723
00:41:22,855 --> 00:41:27,277
BUT MR. TUCKER WANTS ME TO
BELIEVE THAT I'M BEING SELFISH.

724
00:41:27,319 --> 00:41:29,570
HE SAYS NOW THAT I HAVE
THE OPPORTUNITY TO LEAVE,

725
00:41:29,612 --> 00:41:33,574
I SHOULD--
THAT LIANA DESERVES MORE.

726
00:41:37,162 --> 00:41:41,874
MAYBE IT'S TIME I STOPPED
BEING SO AFRAID OF CHANGE.

727
00:41:45,253 --> 00:41:48,340
WILL YOU HELP ME
TAKE MY DAUGHTER HOME?

728
00:41:48,381 --> 00:41:52,010
WE'LL STAY AS LONG AS IT TAKES
TO GET YOUR SHIP FLYING.

729
00:41:52,051 --> 00:41:57,015
THANK YOU, CAPTAIN, BUT ALL
WE NEED ARE THESE COMPONENTS.

730
00:41:57,056 --> 00:41:59,684
I'VE GOT MY OWN CREW
TO DO THE WORK.

731
00:41:59,725 --> 00:42:02,395
SOME OF THEM ARE
PRETTY FAIR ENGINEERS.

732
00:42:02,437 --> 00:42:04,689
I SAW TO THAT.

733
00:42:06,149 --> 00:42:09,027
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

734
00:42:17,743 --> 00:42:19,871
-HOW'S IT GOING?
-GOOD.

735
00:42:19,912 --> 00:42:22,165
WE'RE ABOUT TO START REALIGNING
THE ANTIMATTER INJECTORS.

736
00:42:22,207 --> 00:42:25,377
THAT WAS FAST.

737
00:42:25,418 --> 00:42:28,505
-WHAT'S THAT?
-IT'S A PROTEIN RESEQUENCER.

738
00:42:28,546 --> 00:42:29,755
I FIGURED YOU MUST BE TIRED

739
00:42:29,797 --> 00:42:32,008
OF EATING THE SAME FOOD
ALL THE TIME.

740
00:42:32,050 --> 00:42:35,887
I, UH, PROGRAMMED IT
FOR MAKING ICE CREAM--

741
00:42:35,928 --> 00:42:41,184
ONLY FIVE FLAVORS,
BUT THEY'RE GOOD ONES.

742
00:42:41,226 --> 00:42:42,935
LIANA: ROCKY ROAD?

743
00:42:42,977 --> 00:42:46,356
TUCKER: YOU DIDN'T THINK I'D
SEND YOU OFF WITHOUT ROCKY ROAD?

744
00:42:46,398 --> 00:42:48,649
THANK YOU.

745
00:42:50,443 --> 00:42:52,987
ARE YOU SURE YOU DON'T WANT US
TO STAY FOR A WHILE,

746
00:42:53,029 --> 00:42:54,280
LEND A HAND?

747
00:42:54,322 --> 00:42:56,824
YOU'VE GOT A LOT MORE
PLACES TO GO.

748
00:42:56,866 --> 00:42:58,993
SO DO YOU.

749
00:43:12,257 --> 00:43:14,759
MAYBE I'LL SEE YOU OUT THERE.

750
00:43:15,634 --> 00:43:17,720
I'D LIKE THAT.
